        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">><placeName>Albany</placeName>&#44; <date>Nov. 15&#44; 1849</date></p>
            <p>Peace and greetings to the exalted and beloved scholar and<lb/> rabbi etc. etc.
                    <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Pardon me&#44; Dear Sir&#44; if I trouble you with a small<lb/> matter which is very
                important to me in order to enable me<lb/> to realize my thoughts and hopes to
                arrive at my desired<lb/> sta<del>t</del>tion. I have lived here&#44; in this strange land&#44;
                only<lb/> about a month&#44; and because of my many sins&#44; I have lost in<lb/>
                the course of this short time three young and tender children<lb/> for whose sake I
                left my birth&#8211;place. There I studied for<lb/> about ten years in various
                Yeshiboth under great sages of<lb/> Israel in F&#252;rth and W&#252;rzburg&#44;
                Bavaria&#44; where I was <sic>privi&#8211;<lb/>eleged</sic> to learn<del>s in</del> and teach
                for about twenty years. Be&#8211;<lb/>cause of the vicissitudes of the time&#44;
                however&#44; the source<lb/> of my livelihood was dried up&#44; and I was forced to
                move<lb/> my dwelling place to a far land&#44; and to earn my bread in a<lb/>
                distant place. Now I turn to right and to left o seek where<lb/> I might food for my
                large family and honor God with my wealth<lb/> or my speech&#44; i.e. by finding a
                place and a holy congregation<lb/> with which I might decide to settle. Now&#44;
                since this is not<lb/> the proper time for a general search&#44; for winter is
                here&#44; and<lb/> the cold as well as the difficulties of travel are in the
                way&#44;<lb/> moreover&#44; since the large majority of Jewish congregations of<lb/>
                this land already have cantors and rabbis while only here and<lb/> there are there
                any which announce that they are in search of<lb/> teachers&#44; scribes&#44;
                hazanim&#44; and shochtim&#44; therefore I thought<lb/> that while sitting still and
                doing nothing&#44; it might be well<lb/> to beg of you to do me the
                    <sic>kndness</sic> and mention me in your<lb/> esteemed periodical&#44; the
                Occident&#44; and find a place for the<lb/> enclosed few lines. I have xxx written
                them in English but<lb/> I have probably sinned against the laws of the language </p>

            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>so&#44; then I beg of you to remove this obstacle and correct<lb/> the error. I have
                as yet been able to attain only a slight<lb/> acquaintance with English.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should I have the good fortune to find quickly a place<lb/> to do sacred work&#44; I
                too may be able to do something to<lb/> help you&#44; xxxxxx <sic>expecially</sic> to
                spread your periodical as<lb/> far as possible&#44; and to be ready ever to serve
                you and seek<lb/> your good and your welfare according to your great worth.<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Isaac Straus</persName><lb/> hazan and rabbi.</p>


        </body>
